The paper discusses the problem of learning from imbalanced multilabel data, which is a common issue in machine learning and data mining. The paper proposes a novel algorithm to address the problem of difficult minority labels in imbalanced multilabel datasets. The paper also presents specific metrics to assess this trait in multilabel datasets. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
